/*
 * Simple whitelist of names in the combat logs that are considered to be "real-players" by default. PvP damage is calculated
 * when a real-player heals, or does DPS, to another real-player. However, the APP has no way of knowing if a player is real or not
 * based on the logs alone, so it uses a learning process to determine what is and what isn't a player. (using various heuristic techniques
 * like if a player opens their glider) However, the learning process takes time, and in order to have accurate stats for fresh app installs,
 * this seed table provides a top 500 non-NPC names list. All of these strings are either hashed character names, or other words that are not used by NPCs in the game.
 * Players changing their in-game names will have no effect on this list, as these are non-NPC names only. The alternative was loading a LUA addon and scanning,
 * which some other addons do, but this felt like a more elegant solution that doesn't require any extra setup from the user. These hashes are not reversible, the
 * original names were discarded after hashing.
